24 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 290, \"to\": 312}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee, a three-time NCAA champion for the Hawkeyes, went 4-0 at the World Olympic Games Qualifier.\", \"from\": 333, \"to\": 429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 333, \"end\": 336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.6057131702269353, \"rank\": 0.6508419099497167, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9998551024138206, \"rank\": 8.71990408174426e-05, \"text\": \"NCAA champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Division_I_Wrestling_Championships\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Hawkeyes\", \"from\": 369, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Olympic Games Qualifier\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 428}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee defeated Ben Tarik of Morocco by technical superiority in just 22 seconds, securing a takedown before locking up four exposures in a leg lace to put the match away.\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 431, \"end\": 434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.6057131702269353, \"rank\": 0.6508419099497167, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 448, \"end\": 453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tariq_ibn_Ziyad\", \"score\": 0.9988735838446912, \"rank\": 0.001127686399480598, \"text\": \"Tarik\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tariq_ibn_Ziyad\", \"dbpedia\": \"htt